LIMPOPO Provincial Commissioner LT. General Nneke Ledwaba has condemned the ongoing killings and assaults on women. ALSO READ: JEALOUS BOYFRIEND KILLS ZOLILE! Ledwaba's condemnation follows the arrest of a 45-year-old man for killing his wife and attempting to kill another man at Matobole village, outside Lebowakgomo. Police spokesperson Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said, it is alleged the 33-year-old Sana Kgwale was shot to death by her husband after a domestic dispute. He said after the murder, it is believed that the suspect wrapped Kgwale's body with a blanket and hid it in the bathtub before he handed himself over to the cops. Investigations have revealed that the couple had an argument, whereby the husbandÂ  accused the wife of having an affair with another man. Ngoepe said the motive behind the shooting, is not yet clear at this stage but domestic violence may not be ruled out. The injured man was taken to hospital with a serious gunshot wounds for medical treatment. The suspect will appear in the Lebowakgomo Magistrate's Court soon. 